 into, or leaving your online friends but sooner or later you come to the conclusion that its just not worth the hassles anymore. The EQ economy has gotten horrendously out of hand and that was a design flaw from the beginning as well. Too many ways for cash to come into the world and not enough ways for it to leave...thus inflation has gotten out of hand. Honestly Id felt this way about EQ since the beginning of this year but was hanging out with someone who was new to the game which made it fun for me again for a time too. But soon as that person hit the high 50s the glaring flaws of the game design became apparant to them too. Its nothing an expansion will fix, its the way the game was designed. So no, I wont be back and I'm honestly happier not playing EQ than when I was.  Eq was fun because it was novel but over time it's become old and after playing it for so long one becomes aware of the aspects of the game that just dont work to keep me wanting to shell out my time and money to keep playing it. People tend to like to put things that were &quot;firsts&quot; on a pedastle and I see a lot of that going on here. For those of you who are all gung-ho, &quot;yaaay EQ&quot;, who started this year...nothing I or anyone else can say will alter your opinion but I want you to remember this thread and see how you feel about it in another 6 months to a year. Sure EQ was a first and it was cool....but Model-Ts were a first and were cool too but I dont see too many of them on the roads today. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usagemonprayeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sagemon Prayeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/24/01 8:17:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=